# Pre-commit Rules for Claude Code Exporter v2

## Automated Checks (Run by Husky)

1. **Linting**
   - ESLint with TypeScript rules
   - Check for unused variables
   - Enforce async/await best practices
   - No floating promises

2. **Type Checking**
   - TypeScript compiler with --noEmit
   - Strict mode enabled
   - No implicit any

3. **Code Formatting**
   - Prettier for consistent style
   - Auto-fix on commit

4. **Tests**
   - Unit tests must pass
   - Coverage thresholds enforced
   - No skipped tests allowed

5. **Complexity Analysis**
   - Cyclomatic complexity < 10
   - Max function length: 50 lines
   - Max file length: 300 lines
   - Max depth: 4 levels

## SOLID Principles Checklist

Before committing, verify:

- [ ] **Single Responsibility**: Each class/function has one reason to change
- [ ] **Open/Closed**: New features added via extension, not modification
- [ ] **Liskov Substitution**: Subtypes are substitutable for base types
- [ ] **Interface Segregation**: No client forced to depend on unused methods
- [ ] **Dependency Inversion**: Depend on abstractions, not concretions

## Clean Code Checklist

- [ ] Functions do ONE thing
- [ ] Descriptive variable and function names
- [ ] No magic numbers (use constants)
- [ ] No commented-out code
- [ ] Tests are readable and maintainable

## Security Checklist

- [ ] No hardcoded credentials
- [ ] Input validation on all external data
- [ ] No SQL injection vulnerabilities
- [ ] Dependencies are up to date
- [ ] No console.log() in production code

## Performance Checklist

- [ ] No N+1 queries
- [ ] Proper database indexes
- [ ] Pagination for large datasets
- [ ] Caching strategy implemented
- [ ] No memory leaks

## Documentation Requirements

- [ ] JSDoc comments for public APIs
- [ ] README updated if needed
- [ ] ADRs for architectural decisions
- [ ] Migration guide for breaking changes